The '''Mage Arena''' is a [[members]]-only area located deep in the [[Wilderness]]. It is a large arena where multiple battle mages affiliated with the three [[gods]] are gathered, and the starting point for the [[miniquests]] [[Mage Arena I]] and [[Mage Arena II]].

After completion of these miniquests, players will receive the three [[god spells]], [[God Staff|staffs]] and [[God capes|capes]].
[[File:Mage Arena bank map.png|thumb|A map of the bank and the connected area.|220px]]

==Miniquest==
Before the player can cast god spells or access the [[Mage Arena]], players must complete the Mage Arena [[miniquest]]. The Mage Arena Bank and [[Lundail's Arena-side Rune Shop|Rune Shop]] can still be used without completion of the miniquest.

==Lower level==
After completion of [[Mage Arena I]], players are able to access the Mage Arena's lower level, where three of the god statues are located as well as the [[Mage Arena Staffs]] shop. Here, after completion of the miniquest, players can pray to one of the three god statues and obtain a cape affiliated with that god.

In addition, the player will receive one free [[god staff]] from the staff merchant depending on the god they chose during the miniquest, whilst the other two must be bought for 80,000 [[coins]] each.

==Stores==
*[[Lundail's Arena-side Rune Shop]], accessible at any level.
*[[Mage Arena Staffs]], accessible after completion of the Mage Arena minigame (detailed above).
*A [[bank]] and its banker; [[Gundai]]

==Charging spells==
Players who wish to use the three [[god spells]] outside of the Mage Arena must charge them first by casting them 100 times inside the arena on the [[battle mage]]s walking around the arena. The spell does not have to deal damage to count toward the 100 required casts. This only has to be done once.

Once you have charged a spell, you will receive a message saying you are now able to cast the spell outside the arena.

The aggressiveness of the battle mages depends on the god cape worn by the player; mages are not aggressive to players wearing their God's cape.

[[Protect from Magic]] is recommended for fighting battle mages. As the spells they attack with can hit up to 20, it is recommended to bring [[prayer potion]]s and [[food]]. However, players possessing high [[Magic]] and [[Defence]] levels may find it more economical to use food instead.

==Player killing==
The Mage Arena bank is often called 'Mage Bank'. It is one of only two banks in the entire [[Wilderness]] (the other being in the [[Ferox Enclave]]), and one of the few areas in the Wilderness where players cannot attack other players.

This makes the Mage Arena a [[player killing]] hotspot as people training the god spells will almost always have a valuable drop in [[blood rune]]s as well as a bank area for those farming items or needing to restock after a fight with a [[Wilderness boss]].

Player killers often use the [[Tele Block]] spell here to prevent players from pulling the lever and escaping to the Mage Bank.

Inside the arena, player killers cannot attack players who are fighting [[Kolodion]] during the events of [[Mage Arena I]] miniquest, but are able to after the quest's completion. In addition, some player killers may even dress themselves as the [[Battle mage|Saradomin battle mage]] in the arena, usually in the attempt to ambush players. However, this is not common. Be careful not to attack the disguised player, as you will become [[Skull (status)|skulled]].

As the inside of the Mage Arena is still considered part of the Wilderness, and located at Level 52 Wilderness, teleports will not work inside the arena.

